dataList.title: Los Mariachis
dataList.content: Uh… What are you supposed to be…?

dataList.title: Yurodivy
dataList.content: Made new friends in the meantime, have you, Rodya?
Sonya laid his hand of cards open on the table.

dataList.title: Yurodivy
dataList.content: You win, Rodion. I have no objections.
He then left through the door and didn’t return.
Instead, a deafeningly hollow clap suddenly filled the room.

dataList.title: Los Mariachis
dataList.content: Haha, caramba… I enjoyed the spectacle, but…

dataList.title: Los Mariachis
dataList.content: I’m not as cool as Sonya.

dataList.title: Los Mariachis
dataList.content: Since you brought your friends, why don’t I introduce some of mine as well?
…Y’know, uh, I’m pretty sure I heard a member of your Syndicate say that gambling was purely entertainment for you.

dataList.title: Los Mariachis
dataList.content: Mhm. So isn’t this more entertaining than accepting defeat right away?
You were gonna push on with force regardless of who won, weren’t you?

dataList.title: Los Mariachis
dataList.content: Pfh. Think about it. I have strength and manpower, so why would I give up on the Golden Bough ‘cause a round or three of a game said so?
Aight, then. I’m actually glad you’re a rebel.
I was starting to get bored of sitting around too.
